An International Organization, Pan African Youths Union, has conferred the ” 2020 African Youths Role Model Award,” on the Chairman, Jega Local Government Council, Kebbi State, Alhaji Shehu Mashal Jega. The conferment of the prestigious award was contained in a letter signed by the  Union’s Commissioner, Youths Political Participation in Africa, Amb. Oladele John Nihi,on behalf of the President, Amb.Tahina Juliana Ratovoson. The Union has its Head Office in Taif, Khartoum, Sudan. In the letter, the union said that, the award was conferred on Mashal in deep appreciation for his National, Continental and Global selfless and tireless leadership. Part of the letter read,” the award is in view of your National, Continental and Global selfless and tireless mentorship of Nigerian youths in particular and African Youths, in general.” The Union also urged the Awardee to sustain his support, commitment, passion and belief in youths.